begin_memory_text: We talked about how things were going this year with Covid and the fact that he was a comedian who had lost his job and livelyhood since March.
middle_memory_text: We were still talking about Covid but more about how it has affected his industry and what the stand up comedy business is like.
end_memory_text: We were talking about an illness he had had and how he had been in the hospital for 13 months and how hard it would be to be a teenager with Covid right now.
rest_of_day_open: It is only Sunday so it is hard to tell, but I hope that it will go well.  We have a number of fun things to do this week so I am looking forward to those things.  I also don't have any appointments that I am not looking forward to so that is positive.
critical_positive: It was a rather weird conversations but it went ok because he was used to talking.  He pretty much talked the entire time and I just had to sit back and nod and agree.  He is a comedian so he used to having the stage and have people listen to him.
critical_negative: It gets a little boring to be in one sided conversations for very long.  I got kind of tired of listening to him talk and then having him not really be interested in what I had to say very much.  He was a funny guy so it wasn't too bad really.

begin_memory_text: If I remember correctly, I think that we started out talking about surveys. After introductions, I mean. It was nice to talk to somebody who can relate to the little details of everything.
middle_memory_text: Stand up comedy and the politics of live events. We talked about my industry and how it works and how live events in general are impossible in this new world.
end_memory_text: Coronavirus and medical stuff. We talked about my health problems, her cousin's comparable problems, and her son's struggles with living under Covid restrictions. We actually had a pretty comprehensive discussion about it.
rest_of_day_open: It's going to be rough. I've been depending on Congress passing another stimulus bill in order to stave off eviction, but it's looking more and more like they're just going to let the country fall apart. I can't do anything, really. All I can do is wait and see. It's nightmarish. I'll be stressed and watching news every day.
critical_positive: We had a lot of points of relation, so it was a nice, easy-going conversation. We easily slid from topic to topic without any gaps or awkward lulls in conversation. She was good at asking questions to move it along without me having to worry about it too much. It was nice.
critical_negative: I probably didn't ask quite enough questions of her. She kept asking me things, so I just followed her lead and chatted happily about whatever came up. There was a little crosstalk, but I think that's due to both of us having assertive personalities and probably both being a little gabby, in general.
